# Frontend Docker build context should only ever need the app source.
# Without this file, `docker compose build` (context: .) tries to tar up
# the entire /opt/apps/eagle-amsterdam tree, including the self-hosted
# Supabase data/secrets directories — which the `deploy` user correctly
# cannot read (Postgres data dir is 0700, owned by the postgres container's
# uid). See SETUP_LOG.md section 18 for the incident this caused.

.git
node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Self-hosted Supabase infra (server-only, not part of the frontend build)
supabase/

# One-time Lovable Cloud migration data (PII, password hashes)
migration-data/

# Docs, ops scripts, logs — not needed inside the image
*.md
*.log
logs
backup.sh
deploy.sh

# Editor directories and files
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
